With the Auda-Taller tool, the Audatex company ensures that the user gets a budget in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search the replacement, create the budget and generate budget.
The ease of use is an essential conditioner for these systems, especially to convince older professionals, who tend to be more or less reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 tourism, 109 all-terrain, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it you need a computer with internet connection.
Once the model has been identified to be repaired using its base number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as labour price, reloads or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a rating tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop orientation does not include estimated labour times.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is EUR 350 per year, which the customer can finance.
Currently the Audatex company is working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with very good eyes, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it around to see the inner face.
